🔑 DSA Pattern / Concept
Pattern: Dynamic Programming (Unbounded Knapsack)

Why?

You can use each coin unlimited times.

You want the minimum number of coins to reach exactly X.

This is the unbounded knapsack problem with target sum X.

🧩 Algorithm
Initialize a DP array dp of size X+1 with large values (e.g., 1e9).

Set dp[0] = 0 (0 coins needed to make sum 0).

For each amount i from 1 to X:

For each coin c:

If i - c >= 0, update:

